[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering bootstrap class issues**\n\nI'm thinking about how the bootstrap class needs to reference `org.apache.xml.resolver`, but if it's not booted, then it can't see the app. I wonder if some tests for XMLCatalog might require the resolver too. Maybe I need to add the xml-resolver jar? It could be possible to append the entire testRuntimeClasspath to the bootclasspath, but that might include junit/assertj/test classes, which could complicate things. Plus, the classes directory isn't a jar, so I need to figure that out.\n\n**Examining Ant tests**\n\nI need to consider the existing Ant tests related to global boot. The `AntTest` is using the Ant task from ant.jar for boot and involves the Project boot. There might be XML classes from JDK used in the build file parser within the Project helper. Additionally, the `XSLTProcessTest` seems to use the XSLTProcess class, likely from the ant-trax artifact. It’s an interesting setup to analyze!\n\n**Reviewing build.gradle issues**\n\nI noted that earlier tests utilized \"init.\" That's fine, but there's something off with the line numbers in the build.gradle file due to an old diff without an offset. I really need to double-check the relevant sections to make sure everything is aligned correctly. Is there anything else I should consider about this? It feels sort of quirky, but I'll keep digging!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ec11b8f7823f2c60169f5554aee50819daef06d7609d14f43\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9VVlOzI230KC4HJgvJfplmYulUwxeJebJBKKvqbmbkiLplQT61ueXrBx37WNzicIydAQBK3ZXRSHLWLgz6D4k9HLZ1kI_pI8Li25YJnQdTwauLyO8nQgTvRU1Ub_AutwxAV2D3zyra7Fb9ypIy-AQ9zQq6hXIHfbrz1lZx5DCtvPcI7Gf24mB1pybTCGLHdUA4tEt5g33xqUA-RR6xK8D2MHXRkjE2-rxdkbuY1baDbKxoVsVtGwWTGTY_AXJg1k1OhTLoYZSYRJSQiwOzyC8qRrqqsN3iaJSWe_JxD9pY2Z0a8GG8WnvYgPoeRjIG76FAnH20mySC3rzNCJpnnQLCDfjJ9Xh41k1cHzj_XnMQXxNp2bxujU-dsq9cXxQEUi