e I can use public API via MethodHandles, direct reflection isn't allowed. Modifying bytecode is also a no-go. I might try configuring a test fork specifically for AvailableTest, but it gets trickier given dependencies with the tck task.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing custom test tasks**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out if a custom test task could help with dynamic coverage. I wonder if I can configure the default `test` to exclude AvailableTest, but I might need to include it in a separate task. However, the root tck may only execute the standard `test` task. I could set it up so `test` is finalized by `availableBootstrapTest`, but I need to consider if nativeTest depends on test and finalizers. If tests fail, that could complicate things, especially if the dynamic access report relies on test.exec.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test configurations**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out if excluding `AvailableTest` from the test means `nativeTest` won't be included, which isn't ideal. I wonder if I should split the test file into normal tests and bootstrap-only ones using a JUnit condition. It looks like I can't skip native tests. I might need to run a normal `test` without bootclasspath and a custom `availableBootstrapTest` enabled by a system property. It’s a bit complex, and I feel like I’m going in circles with these conditions!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing testing issues**\\n\\nI'm wondering if skipping the normal test is really the best option. It seems like the failure is due to the global bootclasspath preventing the bootstrap Ant from accessing the application classpath. Maybe I could append all test classes and runtime classpath to the bootclasspath globally so bootstrap classes can see the fixtures too. Also, there's a null pointer exception in `Locator.getResourceSource` because the ClassLoader variable `c` is null, which is unexpected. I should take a closer look at line 108 in Locator.\"}]}"}